            </footnote>
            <footnote ID="I02182012680911e88f4a9c1f64101294">
                <label.designator>4</label.designator>
                <footnote.body>
                    <para>
                        <bop/>
                        <bos/>
                        <paratext>The Panel&apos;s inability and unwillingness to enter orders for transfer or remand
                            conditioned on some substantive or procedural requirement of the Panel are discussed in §§ <cite.query
                                    w-ref-type="NA" w-normalized-cite="MDLITMANs3:10" w-pub-number="185218"
                                    ID="I02195890680911e88f4a9c1f64101294">3:10
                            </cite.query> and  <cite.query w-ref-type="NA" w-normalized-cite="MDLITMANs3:11"
                                                           w-pub-number="185218" ID="I0219a6b0680911e88f4a9c1f64101294">
                                3:11</cite.query>.
                            <eos/>
                            <bos/>These orders should not be confused with conditional transfer orders and conditional
                            remand orders that are properly entered by the Panel.
                            <eos/>
                            <bos/>These latter orders are conditional only in that they become final if not objected to,
                            but have no effect if a party files a notice of objection.
                            <eos/>
                            <bos/>Conditional transfer orders are discussed in §§ <cite.query w-ref-type="NA"
                                                                                              w-normalized-cite="MDLITMANs4:6"
                                                                                              w-pub-number="185218"
                                                                                              ID="I021a1be0680911e88f4a9c1f64101294">
